Installation:
    1. Followed the instructions here for debian package: http://cassandra.apache.org/download/

    2. Did the following:
         a.  echo "deb http://www.apache.org/dist/cassandra/debian 311x main" | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/sources.list.d/cassandra.sources.list
         b. curl https://www.apache.org/dist/cassandra/KEYS | sudo apt-key add -
         c. sudo apt-get update
         d. sudo apt-get install cassandra

    3. Check for status:
        a) service cassandra status
        b) systemctl status cassandra.service

    4. Looks like cassandra-driver was installed using pip:
          pip install cassandra-driver.
       This cassandra-driver is from Datastax

Configuration:
    1. Edited /etc/cassandra/cassandra.yaml and changed:
         a. data_file_directories:
                 - /data/data3/cassandra/data (prev was /var/lib/cassandra/data)

Procedures:
    1. Moving cassandra directories - esp. the data dir
          a. Stop cassandra (service cassandra stop)
          b. Create a new data (or other) dir.
          c. Copy or move old data to new data dir.
          d. Make sure the new dir is owned by "cassandra"
          e. Make sure the new dir groups is "cassandra"
          f. Make sure that the dir and files are writable
          g. Change the configuration per above
          h. Start cassandra (service cassandra start)


